Aftermath:
•	Disable the device’s network connection capabilities remotely
•	Report affected employee’s access credentials and device’s IP address to CrispyGen’s IT staff immediately
•	Change all of the affected employee’s passwords
•	Delete all current passwords through Google Chrome’s Sync settings.
•	Set time bombs on data. If the device has not been connected to CrispyGen’s network for a set period of time, the work related data on the device should be wiped.
•	Keep an up-to-date backup of all data relating to CrispyGen’s work so that no important data is lost